if you are offered a snack to go with your tea, please note that you will be charged for it, even if you don't eat any. in some cases scam artists may ask to split the really high bill and convince the victim to pay at least half of it. a variant of this scam may happen when you are invited by "art students" to shabby art shops and pressured to buy overpriced reproductions. having said that, while it is important to avoid being scammed, it is very common for curious english-speaking chinese to genuinely start a conversation with you, 